[{'comment_id': 665756149, 'comment_body': "Looks like these two can be refactored by quite a bit. 

For example this helper could be implemented as (I swapped the arg order to keep compile-time arguments earlier in the argument list, out of personal taste and somewhat of convention):

```chapel
  proc getIndicesDefinition(param rank, shape: domain) {
    type eltType = if rank==1 then int else rank*int;
    var indices: [shape] eltType;
    return indices;
  }
```

You can either implement the one above similarly, or even better, it could be just:

```chapel
proc getSampleDefinition(param rank, numElements: int) {
  return getIndicesDefinition(rank, {0..<numElements});
}
```

Also, do you anticipate these functions to be useful for the user?  (I don't) If not, you should make them `private proc`
